key_points: Vice President Kamala Harris is set to travel to Singapore and Vietnam from August 20 to August 26.
The trip aims to promote the message 'America is back' and signal the Biden-Harris Administration's interest in Asia.
The visit will emphasize the importance of comprehensive engagement and strategic partnerships in Asia.
Harris will discuss trade, security, including issues in the South China Sea, and promote economic cooperation.
The visit will include meetings with government officials, leaders from the private sector, and civil society leaders.
Key areas of discussion will include regional security, the Covid-19 pandemic, and climate change.
Harris will be the first vice president ever to visit Vietnam.
This will be Harris's first trip to the region as vice president and her second international trip since taking office.
The trip underscores the Biden Administration's effort to counter China's growing influence through democratic partnerships in the region.
President Biden has not yet traveled to the region since taking office but has hosted leaders from Japan and South Korea.
